article.description: Quincy McKnight scored 25 points, made all nine of his free throw attempts and had four steals and Seton Hall erupted in the second half for a 75-55 win over Prairie View A&M on Sunday.
article.headline: Seton Hall turns it around, downs Prairie View A&M by 20 PTs
article.linkText: Seton Hall turns it around, downs Prairie View A&M by 20 PTs
article.story: SOUTH ORANGE, N.J. -- Quincy McKnight scored 25 points, made all nine of his free throw attempts and had four steals and Seton Hall erupted in the second half for a 75-55 win over Prairie View A&M on Sunday. Anthony Nelson, Jared Rhoden and Tyrese Samuel each scored 12 for Seton Hall (8-4). The Pirates shot 7 of 23 in the first half -- including all seven missed 3-point attempts -- and Prairie View led 27-22 at halftime. Seton Hall then turned it around shooting 57.6% (19 of 33) and outscored the Panthers 53-28. Darius Williams scored 19 for the Panthers (3-9), Gerard Andrus scored 14 and Devonte Patterson 11. Seton Hall starts Big East Conference action when it travels to DePaul on Dec. 30. After a Dec. 30 home contest against NAIA-member Huston-Tillotson, the Panthers begin Southwestern Athletic Conference play Jan. 4 at home against Alcorn State. ----- More AP college basketball: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and https://twitter.com/AP-Top25
